Aqua Cultured Foods,summary:Aqua Cultured Foods is dedicated to feeding the world more sustainably by focusing on its mission to offer nutrient-rich foods in the form of fungi-based seafood alternatives that will feed the next two billion people to be born on the planet, all while protecting the oceans from the detrimental impact of overfishing. We're creating the first \u201cwhole cut\u201d fermentation-derived seafood alternatives. Our technology allows us to biomanufacture a sustainable seafood analog through the growth and fermentation of mycelium. Aqua Cultured Foods has developed novel protein fermentation technology that produces seafood alternatives with the appearance, texture, taste and nutritional content of conventional seafood -- and without microplastics, mercury, antibiotics, PCBs, parasites, or a high risk of foodborne illness.This technology can be leveraged across platforms to create different types of seafood including shrimp, calamari, sushi cuts and fish filet substitutes. \n\nAnne Palermo is the CEO & Co-Founder of Aqua Cultured Foods, a leading future food startup in the alt protein space. After recently closing the largest pre-seed round in alt seafood, Anne is focused on using Aqua\u2019s novel fermentation technology to bring to market nutritionally superior, hyper-realistic, whole cuts of seafood alternatives. Anne began her career in finance before transitioning into food tech, food science and culinary innovation with the launch of her first cpg company. While there, she developed proprietary technology pertaining to manufacturing processes and the product formulations used in a high protein snacking platform. She quickly scaled the company to a multimillion dollar run We enable Mom & Pop Retailers with seamless procurement (app-based ordering and next day delivery), simplified payments and access to working capital (through Buy-Now Pay-Later credit). Our project was inspired by a larger question. When you look back at your life, are there  moments you wish you could relive? Cities you could revisit? Old friends you could reconnect with? Loved ones you could appreciate once more? I think as we get older we find ourselves asking these questions more and more. And currently there aren’t great ways to reminisce these moments in life. We used to have photo albums.. but that’s it. This is what inspired Everly - we want to reimagine how we reminisce.

Outside of Everly, I am  a Director at 151 Capital, an alternative investment managers that focuses on delivering non-market directional, bespoke strategies to its investors.

I enjoy cultivating new ideas and delivering them through best execution. I believe in working with absolute integrity, working with folks who possess absolute integrity, and positioning them in a way where they can be the best version of themselves. My friends and colleagues would describe me as witty, authentic and adaptable. They would also tell you I can be impatient, and at times, a little too honest. 

If you’d like to connect, don’t hesitate to reach out. I’d love to hear your story, and I’m sure we’ll learn something new along the way.

COMPANY DETAILS:
Lucidiam is the maker of Unitii.

Unitii is a platform that unifies and ranks work from multiple sources for MSPs (Managed Service Providers).

MSP users login to one app instead of multiple and perform their work from a single simple interface.

MSPs benefit by:
- Crushing their SLAs
- Increasing their margins
- Increasing client retention
- Taking on more clients (scaling)
- Decreasing personnel churn

How:
- Saves time by eliminating switching and prioritizing work across tabs & apps
- Doesn't replace existing systems
- Connects via APIs
- Sets up in 30 mins
- Data stays in your cloud (you own your data)

Live Demo Here: https://www.lucidiam.com/live-demo.html

Presagen is The Social Network for Healthcare, a decentralized online platform that connects clinics and patients globally, enables collaboration and data sharing through incentives, democratizes the creation of globally scalable AI healthcare products, and protects data privacy and ownership. Sustainable Ocean Alliance,summary:Doreen (\Dory\) has dedicated her career to supporting social entrepreneurs and accelerating climate and sustainability solutions. She is passionate and committed to working with founders, funders, and operators to tackle the impacts of climate change on our planet Earth.

Doreen first launched her career in venture as one of the founding members of Alumni Ventures Group’s Social Impact Fund (UN SDGs-focused fund) and Towerview Ventures (Duke affiliate fund). She then helped a Fortune 500 company lead their technology scouting engagements with Silicon Valley and the global tech community. In 2020, Doreen joined Republic as a Venture Partner to help democratize access to early stage investments and support to underrepresented founders and their startup ideas. Today, she is focused on supporting ocean-based climate solutions with the Sustainable Ocean Alliance and its affiliate fund, Seabird Ventures (ImpactAssets 50 Emerging Impact Fund).

In addition to her commitment to work on climate and sustainability, Doreen is an advocate for building more diverse, equitable, and inclusive communities. She is a member of the Women in VC, Women in Climate Tech, and My Climate Journey communities. Doreen is also a Board Member of Diversity VC's North America / U.S. Chapter and Duke Northern California (NorCal) Region.

Doreen has a bachelor’s degree in Materials Science and Engineering from the University of California at Berkeley and a professional master's degree in Environmental Engineering from Duke University. Autocrypt,summary:[Introduction]
I'm the leader of strategy in AutoCrypt that is the automotive cybersecurity company. Our identity is Secure Mobility Platform Provider. Now, we closed Series-B round with an investment of 28m$, and we start to open Series-C soon. So we want to meet various investor, VCs and PEs. Our company is selected for the Forbes 100 startups to watch.
#Series-C
#Investor #VCs #PEs
#Forbes

[Our Viewpoint of Market] - Cooperative Autonomous Driving
Currently, various autonomous driving companies using sensors, control solutions, and computer vision are appearing, but these are independent autonomous driving systems that make only vehicles smarter. In order for autonomous driving to be commercialized faster and to create real autonomous driving, it is necessary to create cooperative autonomous driving in which not only the vehicle but also the infrastructure becomes smart.
#Cooperative_Autonomous_Driving
#Smart_Vehicle
#Smart_Infrastructure

[Our Solution] - V2X, IVS(In-vhiecle-system security), V2G
For this, we provide communication (V2X, Vehicle-to-Everything) that connects the car and all things, provide in-vehicle security (IVS, In-Vehicle System) to ensure that the connected vehicle is safe, and with the change of electrification, we provide a power grid connection (V2G, Vehicle-to-Grid) that provides various services by connecting to the power grid.
#V2X(Vehicle-to-Everything
#IVS(In-Vehicle-System Security)

Jamie left the UAE to join hands with his brother, Daniel to build a property development business, specialising in the development of student accommodation and residential projects. Following the growth of NEXA, Jamie & Daniel Co-Founded the proptech platform, Zump (www.zump.me). Zump is a new social network for property; removing barriers and connecting owners, buyers and professionals in one platform to create more opportunity for everyone.

Everyday Robots,summary:Jasmine Lawrence currently serves as a Product Manager at Everyday Robots where they are building a new type of learning robot— one that can learn by itself, to help anyone with (almost) anything. Slalom,summary:Slalom Ventures Accelerator (SVA) is a startup accelerator that's all about connecting our customers to innovative startups.  The goal is to match startup solutions to our customer pain points, providing additional value to our customers, strengthening our client relationships, and providing market traction to startups.\n\nWe look for startups creating solutions that address needs our customers face.  B2B startups, targeting mid-to enterprise customers, have the opportunity to join our accelerator program.  Once accepted, the startup will work directly with some of our twelve thousand plus consultants that are working in a variety of markets.  These consultant-advisors will help the startups connect to our marquee customers and partners. These connections can help shape product/market fit through customer interviews, pilots, and even direct sales.  Gaining this market traction not only accelerates growth, but positions the startups for follow-on funding with our venture partners.\n\nSo, if you\u2019re in the business of helping companies do a better job in financial services, entertainment, CPG, retail, or any of our market verticals, we want to hear from you. Or if you have an innovative way of helping our customers deploy and use Salesforce, AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud, we want to hear from you too.  \n\n***Slalom is a global consulting firm focused on strategy, technology, and business transformation. In 41 markets around the world, Slalom's teams have autonomy to move fast and do what's right. They are backed by regional innovation hubs, a global culture of collaboration, and partnerships with the world's top technology providers. Founded in 2001 and headquartered in Seattle, Slalom has organically grown to over 11,000 employees. Slalom has been named one of Fortune's 100 Best Companies to Work For six years running and is regularly recognized by employees as a best place to work. OOTify,summary:Copy/paste from LinkedIn below :)

Ravi Sharma is an investor with 10+ years experience in structured finance and also, an operator with 7+ years experience in human and planetary health. 

Most recently, Ravi built out a venture capital studio for active investment of personal and syndicated capital to underrepresented founders in tech-enabled businesses via iBOS Ventures. Industries include, but are not limited to: planetary health, fintech, digital health, B2B, and web3 (crypto). 

At iBOS, he incubated and founded OOTify (proof-of-care mental health web3 platform) after losing his tennis partner and family members to mental illness. Ravi believes that solving the navigation and utilization issues in mental healthcare is the issue of our generation.

Prior to iBOS and OOTify, Mr. Sharma was a portfolio manager at Western Asset Management Co. (Western Asset) and was personally responsible for approximately $1.3 billion AUM (assets under management). Prior to Western Asset, he worked at PNMAC Capital Management, Arch Bay Capital, and Bank of America Merrill Lynch. He also successfully had two (2) exits in healthcare and clean-technology in 2010 as an operator.

He currently also volunteers as an advisor on the board of the Volunteers of America Community Health Incubator, which is sponsored by the Humana Foundation to launch and scale social enterprises that improve quality, equity and access to care for at-risk populations.

Ravi completed his education at the University of Southern California and his latest passion project is a Children's Mental Health Book he wrote after recently becoming a father. The book speaks to physical health and mental health parity and is a great conversation starter to start talking about mental health early. More information is available here: www.ootify.com/book.,types:[{can_swipe:true,can_meet:true,type_id:6134,type_key_translation_en-gb:Attendee,type_key_translation_en:Attendee,type_key_translation:Attendee,container_id:4431,type_key:attendee},{can_swipe:true,can_meet:true,type_id:6237,type_key_translation_en-gb:Attendee,type_key_translation_en:Attendee Expo Only,type_key_translation:Attendee Expo Only,container_id:4685,type_key:attendeeexpoonly}],type_id:6237,date_created:1651852266,words:null,last_name:Sharma,groups:[{access:hybrid,group_id:5452,group_name:Hybrid,is_speed_networking_group:0}],type_category_id:1,uri:/1/container/4431/thing/6482777,promotion_level:normal,job_industry:null,type_key:attendeeexpoonly,default_access:hybrid,type_key_translation_en-gb:Attendee,sessions_attending:[103203,103204,98930,98929,102241,98942,98939,98932,98941,98933,98934,98940,98937,98943,103207],location:Orange, California, United States of America,type_key_translation:Attendee,did_answer_yes:0},{metadata:null,picture_url:https://events-cdn.grip.events/things-images/3fc5e6c057b49f6f004032725b766344_1663626756.png,type_key_translation_en:Attendee Expo Only,registration_id:null,promoted:0,sessions_speaking:[],location_lng:null,last_joined_group_ids_en-gb:5452,promotion_locations:[],id:6856716,job_title:null,location_lat:null,default_meeting_location:null,swipe_message_date_sent:null,can_meet:1,active:1,last_joined_group_ids:5452,application_id:780,company_name:TravelMeetEat, Inc.,name:Rawle Annandsingh,needs_activation:0,container_id:[4685],date_updated:1663627696,gps_lat:null,gps_lng:null,can_swipe:1,location_code:en-gb,group_ids:[5452],categories:null,swipe_message:null,first_name:Rawle,headline:Co-Founder & CEO - Tychon,summary:We facilitate the seamless collaboration between Brands and Influencers. He is currently at Rice University, sponsored by the Fulbright Program, one of the most prestigious international scholarships of the US Department of State. Risto Trajanov graduated from the Faculty of Computer Science and Engineering, Ss. Cyril and Methodius – Skopje with a “High Achievement” award for completing with a GPA higher than 9.5 (out of 10).
Since 2021, Risto Trajanov has been working as a data scientist, developing a product that would help investors detect greenwashing by providing a platform for monitoring the company’s ESG behavior.
His professional career starts as a teaching mentor for high schoolers learning the programming language Java. He then takes a machine learning internship at the Macedonian Academy Of Sciences And Arts in Skopje. He conducted two machine learning internships, one in Loca Inc., a silicon valley start-up, and the other in Netcetera, a tech company. CEO - Geostry LLC (Everly),summary:I co-created Everly, a platform that delivers a fresh and healthier approach to how we log and share our most cherished moments.

Our project was inspired by a larger question - When you look back at your life, are there moments you wish you could relive? Cities you could revisit? Old friends you could reconnect with? Loved ones you could appreciate once more? I think as we get older we find ourselves asking these questions more and more. Currently there aren’t great ways to reminisce these moments in life. We used to have photo albums but that’s it. This is what inspired Everly - we want to reimagine how we reminisce.

Outside of Everly,  I am a Vice President at Syndigo - a leading eCommerce PIM and Syndication platform company where I am focused on governing and improving the end-to-end flow of data and information.

I take pleasure in bringing ideas to life and sustain it through efficient execution. I enjoy being around creative and high-energy people and put collective minds to solve problems.

If you you’d like to connect, don’t hesitate to reach out. Consultant - Self,summary:I relish innovation - in problem isolation and design of solutions. I deliver them combining technical expertise, continuous learning, execution and leadership. My area of industrial expertise is System Software Performance. I ensure that architecture, design and implementation of a software product is responsive, scales and delights the end-user. My experience spans building and managing a team, KPI, data warehousing, analytics, SoC environment such as ARM processor based Mobile devices and SMP architectures such as Java Enterprise Edition (J2EE).

In a snippet of my work with Motorola, I helped them introduce a mid-tier cell phone called Moto G3 Plus '15 with more RAM world-wide amid bill-of-material cost growth concern so that smart phone users who use many applications in developing countries such as India, Indonesia, Brazil and several African countries can also enjoy a responsive consumer product in this price tier. The plain Moto G3 with half the RAM was also optimized by us and shipped at a lower price point.

I am a Mechanical Engineer (minor Computer Science) with a Ph.D. specializing in Robotics.

Interest Areas: System software performance, Robotics and Control

Industry Experience:
• Ensure architecture, design & implementation of a software product is responsive & scales, delighting the user
• Business level impact on profitability
• Manage, lead, recruit and mentor team
• Innovative multi-tier performance metrics, data warehousing & analytics
• Mobile, enterprise software architecture, multimedia & kernel design review
• Traditional performance optimization analysis
• Solve difficult & intermittent system performance issues
• 20+ years of experience

Research:
• Motion Planning of mechanical parts assembly mating operations with force compliant manipulators
• Sensor integration

Specialties: Embedded and Mobile software platforms, Android, Linux, Kernel and Multimedia Memory Management, Enterprise software performance, J2EE performance, Software scalability, Java AWT Java2D performance, Robotics software for manipulation, Multiprocessors, Sensor integration, Mobile robot navigation, Stereo vision and Task planning,types:[{can_swipe:true,can_meet:true,type_id:6134,type_key_translation_en-gb:Attendee,type_key_translation_en:Attendee,type_key_translation:Attendee,container_id:4518},{can_swipe:true,can_meet:true,type_id:6237,type_key_translation_en-gb:Attendee,type_key_translation_en:Attendee Expo Only,type_key_translation:Attendee,container_id:4685}],type_id:6237,date_created:1656690770,words:null,last_name:Shekhar,groups:[{access:hybrid,group_id:5452,group_name:Hybrid,is_speed_networking_group:0}],type_category_id:1,uri:/1/container/4518/thing/6652518,promotion_level:normal,job_industry:Independent Consultant,default_access:hybrid,type_key_translation_en-gb:Attendee,sessions_attending:[104118,104189,104124,104125],location:Los Altos, California, United States of America,type_key_translation:Attendee,did_answer_yes:0},{metadata:null,picture_url:null,type_key_translation_en:Attendee,registration_id:null,promoted:0,sessions_speaking:[],location_lng:null,last_joined_group_ids_en-gb:5452,promotion_locations:[],id:6789628,job_title:null,location_lat:null,default_meeting_location:null,swipe_message_date_sent:null,can_meet:1,active:1,last_joined_group_ids:5452,application_id:780,company_name:AIX Ventures,name:Shaun Johnson,needs_activation:0,container_id:[4685],date_updated:1662664130,gps_lat:null,gps_lng:null,can_swipe:1,location_code:en-gb,group_ids:[5452],categories:null,swipe_message:null,first_name:Shaun,headline:Partner - IT-Farm literally targets all technology domains, expertise in tech-DD and biz dev support of disruptive game-changer technologies, empowered by his & the team's long history of international business development support including Japan market entry. Example areas include but not limited to medical (hardware/digital/bio), game/entertainment, software, industry 4.0, mobility, food-/ag-tech, environment & energy, electronics, and new materials. Pure pharmaceuticals are exceptionally non-target, while platform technologies are in scope.

Prior to joining IT-Farm, Shinya was an entrepreneur who co-founded/developed new businesses of international and Japanese software tech startups for 20+ years.
